13 years after the birth of his first child, popular comedian, Ayo Makun, aka AY and his wife, Mabel has welcomed another baby. Taking to his Instagram page, the actor and filmmaker, who has been nursing both mother and child, revealed that the newborn is named Ayomide. He wrote; “Our prayers in the last 13 years have been answered. Ayomide thank you for making @realmabelmakun and I, Mummy and Daddy again. Thank you for making Michelle a big sister. Thanks to everyone who kept us in their prayers and never stopped feeding us with positive vibes.” Meanwhile, the AY’s industry colleagues have been sending in their felicitations on the birth of the child. Popular filmmaker, Funke Akindele joined the Makuns in thanksgiving. She wrote; “The Lord is good!! All the time!! My darling sister @realmabelmakun congratulations!! The lord has wiped away your tears, he has put a new song in your mouth. Your joy will be everlasting in Jesus name!!! @aycomedian correct Egbon!! E ku orire sir!!! God bless you and your family more and more.” Flomat Books Opens New Outlet I Won’t Let People Talk Down On My Husband, Says Actress… Also felicitating with the Makuns is actress and filmmaker, Omoni Oboli who offered prayers for the Makuns and their newest member. “To you be ALL the glory! You ALONE could have done this! I worship you King of kings! You deserve ALL our praise our King. Congratulations family @aycomedian @realmabelmakun may God bless our new baby and we cover you all with the blood of the lamb. Ah Mabel many daughters have done well but you excel them all. We love you. We use you as a point of contact to all our mothers in waiting. Don’t give up. Your time has come in Jesus name,” she wrote.